parties.raw_snippet:
This Sponsored Research and License Agreement (this “Agreement”) is entered into on November 28, 2018 (the “Effective Date”), by and
between ArTara, Inc. located at 1 Little West 12th Street, New York, NY 10014 (“ArTara”), and The University of Iowa, located at c/o Division of
Sponsored Programs, 2 Gilmore Hall, Iowa City, IA 52242 (“University”). ArTara and University may individually be referred to herein as a “Party,”
and collectively as “Parties.”
parties.reasoning: The introductory clause explicitly names the contracting entities and states they are the Parties to the Agreement.

contract_type.raw_snippet:
4.2 License. University hereby grants to ArTara an exclusive license to use the Program Data solely for the Project and in Regulatory Filings
in the Field in the Territory.
contract_type.reasoning: The core economic substance is the University granting ArTara an exclusive license and right of reference to use Program Data for regulatory filings, coupled with funding, milestones, and royalties—hallmarks of a license agreement.

notice_period.reasoning: The agreement contains general termination notice provisions (e.g., 30 days) but no automatic renewal or notice-to-prevent-renewal clause.

expiration_date.reasoning: No fixed term or explicit expiration date is stated; only termination rights are provided. There is no explicit perpetual language.

renewal_term.reasoning: The contract does not include any renewal or auto-renewal provision.
